import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['daily_return'] = pd.to_numeric(data['daily_return'], errors='coerce')
    sns.distplot(data['daily_return'], kde=False, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['daily_return'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['daily_return'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of daily returns?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
